flash.tools.debugger.concrete

Interface GetVariableFlag


  • public interface GetVariableFlag
    Flags to the OutGetVariable and OutGetVariableWhichInvokesGetter commands which are sent from the debugger to the player. These values must be kept in sync with 'enum OutGetVariableFlags' in the player's playerdebugger.h file.
    Author:
    mmorearty

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int ALSO_GET_CHILDREN
      Indicates that if the variable which is being retrieved is a compound object (e.g. an instance of a class, as opposed to a string or int or something like that), then the player should also return all of the child members of the object.
      static int DONT_GET_FUNCTIONS
      Indicates that when retrieving children, we only want fields and getters -- we are not interested in regular functions.
      static int GET_CLASS_HIERARCHY
      Indicates that when retrieving children, we also want to know exactly which class each child was defined in.
      static int INVOKE_GETTER
      Indicates that if the variable which is being retrieved is a getter, then the player should invoke the getter and return the result.

    • Field Detail

      • INVOKE_GETTER

        static final int INVOKE_GETTER
        Indicates that if the variable which is being retrieved is a getter, then the player should invoke the getter and return the result. If this flag is *not* set, then the player will simply return the address of the getter itself.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ALSO_GET_CHILDREN

        static final int ALSO_GET_CHILDREN
        Indicates that if the variable which is being retrieved is a compound object (e.g. an instance of a class, as opposed to a string or int or something like that), then the player should also return all of the child members of the object.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DONT_GET_FUNCTIONS

        static final int DONT_GET_FUNCTIONS
        Indicates that when retrieving children, we only want fields and getters -- we are not interested in regular functions. This is an optimization to decrease the amount of network traffic.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • GET_CLASS_HIERARCHY

        static final int GET_CLASS_HIERARCHY
        Indicates that when retrieving children, we also want to know exactly which class each child was defined in. For example, if the variable is of class Foo which extends class Bar, we want to know which member fields came from Foo and which ones came from Bar.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
